TcRuntimeType.description: This BO represents the Document Management Print Configuration runtime properties. This will contain the calculated properties for the print configurations.

TcProperty.description: This is an LOV (Dma1PrintConfigBannerPageLOV) that displays the Banner Page (Off, Single, All). Banner page specifies whether to print a page including the defined stamps and listing additional data.
If true, this will collate the copies printed. Default is false.
This is an LOV (Dma1PrintConfigColorLOV) that will display the supported print configuration colors (e.g. Monochrome, Color) that the user can select.
Represents the number of copies that needs to be printed. The default is 1.
This is an LOV (Dma1PrintConfigOrientationLOV) that will display the supported paper orientations (e.g. Best Fit, Portrait, Landscape).
This is an LOV (Dma1PrintConfigPaperSizesLOV) that will display the supported paper sizes for this print configuration.

This represents the print configuration This represents the available print configuration name/s. Dma1PrintConfigNameLOV will be attached to this property to display the available print configurations that can be selected.
This represents the name of the printer for the selected print configuration.
Specifies a range of pages to print (e.g. 1-5 will print pages 1 to 5).

Specifies the scaling factor, from 0.000001 to 100.0, applied to an image when it's printed.

With standard fit-to-page functionality, the image size is adjusted to fit the paper.
This in an LOV (Dma1PrintConfigSystemStampLOV) to specify whether the system stamp applies to the first page, the banner page, or all pages.
Specifies text for a user stamp to be applied in addition to any existing system stamp configuration.
This indicates if the printing stamp is supported or not.

ServiceInterface.description:
The service provides operations for Active Workspace Document Management batch print.

The getPrinterDefinition operation gets the printer configuration definition information required for the Batch Print action from Active Workspace.
ServiceInterface.name: DocMgmt

OperationTemplate.description: This operation returns Print Configuration definition information from the PrintConfiguration object defined in Teamcenter.
OperationTemplate.name: Dma1::Soa::DocMgmtAw::DocMgmt::getPrinterDefinitions
OperationTemplate.returnDescription:
The Print Configuration definition information. The following partial errors may be returned:

515155 The PrintConfiguration class does not exist in the System

OperationTemplate.description:
Description:
This operation processes the markups on the server.
Use Cases:
    • Load all the existing markups from the server.
    • Save the user created or modified markups to the server.
OperationTemplate.name: Dma1::Soa::DocMgmtAw::DocMgmt::processMarkups
OperationTemplate.returnDescription:
Return the common MarkupResponse that contains the version, message, updated base object, updated markups, and possibly partial errors.

Following are some possible errors return in the ServiceData:
    • 260037 'MARKUP' access privilege on the Item is needed to create or update its Markup.
    • 260038 'MARKUP' access privilege on the Item Revision is needed to create or update its Markup.
    • 260039 'MARKUP' access privilege on the Based Dataset is needed to create or update its Markup.
    • 260040 The Markup cannot be created or updated because the base Dataset is checked-out by somebody else or is out-of-date. Refresh the base Dataset to obtain its latest version.

OperationParameter.description: The version of the markups on the client before the user's modification, set by the server, opaque to the client. For load action, the string is empty. For save action, retrieve the version string from load action response object.
OperationParameter.name: version

OperationParameter.description:
The property map(string, strings). Contain the key/value pairs. Possible values are:
    • Key: “action”. Value: “load” or “save”
    • Key: “message”. Value: “all_users” or “single_user”
    • "all_users" - save or load the markups for all users.
    • " single_user" - save or load the markups for the current user.
OperationParameter.name: properties

OperationParameter.description: A user supplied JSON markup. Empty string is allowed. Valid only for “save” action.
OperationParameter.name: markups

OperationTemplate.description: This operation extracts the contents of the text dataset to a string and returns it or saves the input string to the contents of a text dataset.
OperationTemplate.name: Dma1::Soa::DocMgmtAw::DocMgmt::processTextDataset
OperationTemplate.returnDescription:
The dataset content.

The following partial errors may be returned:
    • 387004 Dataset is not checked out. Unable to update the dataset.
    • 387005 Input object is not a valid text dataset.
    • 387006 Input dataset contains a named reference to a binary file.

OperationParameter.description: For action “load”, this string is to be empty. For action “save”, this string contains the text that is saved as a text file and added as a name reference to the Dataset.
OperationParameter.name: content

OperationParameter.description:
Supported values are:
    • “load” – loads the contents of the text file that is a named reference in the Dataset and returns it in the ProcessTextDatasetResponse. If there is more than one named reference, only the first one is returned.
    • “save” – saves the content string as a text file and adds it as a named reference to the Dataset.
OperationParameter.name: action
